00:00:40.130 --> 00:00:40.530
We're very pleased to have you here.

00:00:42.130 --> 00:00:42.440
This is the 10th year of
the National Book Festival.

00:00:45.220 --> 00:00:45.296
We know you're going to have
a wonderful day here today.

00:00:48.810 --> 00:00:53.076
I want you to know that today,
that our one-hour performance here

00:00:54.270 --> 00:00:57.670
about the Exquisite Corpse
Adventure is being filmed

00:00:58.070 --> 00:00:58.183
for the Library's Web
site and for the archives,

00:01:01.090 --> 00:01:01.313
and you'll have a chance to I hope,

00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:05.800
ask some questions
and also participate.

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:06.776
And we want you to be mindful of
the fact that we have camera risers

00:01:09.650 --> 00:01:09.690
in the back that cannot be tampered
with, or please don't sit on them.

00:01:14.210 --> 00:01:16.610
And also, be careful when you speak,

00:01:18.430 --> 00:01:18.740
you are going to be
recorded as well.

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:20.660
But we think you'll enjoy it
and you'll enjoy the experience.

00:01:24.380 --> 00:01:28.780
What I have here to demonstrate is
the Exquisite Corpse new poster,

00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:29.956
which is available in the back.

00:01:31.890 --> 00:01:32.193
We hope everyone will
take it and remember

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:37.253
that this is a very
wonderful adventure story

00:01:37.880 --> 00:01:40.746
that graphically is
going to be demonstrated

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:42.516
by our two artists today.

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:42.973
And also you're in for a real treat,
because towards the end of this,

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:51.106
you're going to see episode
number 27, which was written

00:01:51.630 --> 00:01:55.696
by our Young People's National
Ambassador, Katherine Paterson,

00:01:57.360 --> 00:01:57.543
and it will be a very
special treat for all of you.

00:02:00.510 --> 00:02:01.510
[ Applause ]

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:10.106
&gt;&gt; John Cole: I want
to begin by recognizing

00:02:10.110 --> 00:02:10.653
that this is the 10th
year of the partnership

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:13.030
between the National Children's
Book and Literacy Alliance

00:02:15.770 --> 00:02:17.636
and the Center for the Book.

00:02:17.770 --> 00:02:18.286
And it has been a fruitful
10-year partnership,

00:02:20.320 --> 00:02:20.830
which has brought us not only
the Exquisite Corpse Adventure,

00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:24.320
but this wonderful group of writers
that are going to be introduced

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:32.166
to you by Mary Brigid Barrett, who
is the President and the Founder,

00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:32.470
and with Katherine
Paterson, a leading life

00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:35.313
in the National Children's
Book and Literacy Alliance.

00:02:38.080 --> 00:02:38.533
I'm pleased to turn this
over to Mary Brigid.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:41.560
Mary Brigid?

00:02:42.560 --> 00:02:43.253
&gt;&gt; Mary Brigid: Thank you, John.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:45.000


00:02:45.060 --> 00:02:46.060
[ Applause ]

00:02:49.350 --> 00:02:49.716
&gt;&gt; Mary Brigid: Good
morning, Washington.

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:54.716
I am Mary Brigid Barrett,
and I'm the President

00:02:58.280 --> 00:02:59.133
of the National Children's
Book and Literacy Alliance.

00:03:00.960 --> 00:03:04.960
And on behalf of the NCBLA Board
of Authors and Illustrators,

00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:08.873
I welcome you to the
Exquisite Corpse Adventure.

00:03:09.640 --> 00:03:12.773
And we'd like to thank
Dr. Billington, Dr. Cole,

00:03:13.530 --> 00:03:17.530
and the incredibly dedicated
staff of the Library of Congress

00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:20.470
for inviting us to be here today.

00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:22.556
Yeah, that's great.

00:03:25.610 --> 00:03:25.740
I have a little housekeeping detail.

00:03:27.880 --> 00:03:30.013
Everybody should have a program.

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:31.113
If you don't have a
program, raise your hand.

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:34.816
And there's going to be a reason
that you need the program,

00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:38.383
so volunteers are going to --

00:03:38.450 --> 00:03:38.760
keep your hands up 'til a
volunteer gets you a program.

00:03:41.740 --> 00:03:41.753
And in this program, you're going
to find all kinds of information

00:03:46.060 --> 00:03:46.320
about the Exquisite
Corpse Adventure,

00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:50.066
what a progressive story is.

00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:50.890
And there's information
about our amazing cast

00:03:53.590 --> 00:03:55.456
of authors and illustrators.

00:03:55.590 --> 00:03:59.190
And also there is a schedule
in the back that tells you

00:04:00.290 --> 00:04:04.290
when our authors will be doing
their individual presentations

00:04:04.330 --> 00:04:05.330
later today.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:06.596
As John -- I don't know,
John didn't mention this,

00:04:09.330 --> 00:04:13.463
but the Exquisite Corpse Adventure
has been read all year round

00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:17.240
by literally thousands
of students and kids

00:04:17.540 --> 00:04:20.540
around the United States
and around the world.

00:04:21.650 --> 00:04:24.516
We have readers from
South Africa and Japan.

00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:26.130
We have readers for
the Exquisite Corpse

00:04:27.530 --> 00:04:28.050
that are reading the story
on Read.gov in Europe.

00:04:30.210 --> 00:04:30.356
So it's been very exciting for us.

00:04:32.330 --> 00:04:32.920
And on top of that,
teachers and librarians

00:04:34.540 --> 00:04:34.593
and parents are using the
Exquisite Corpse with all

00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:38.863
of the educational materials, and
they're getting the young people

00:04:41.110 --> 00:04:44.443
in their lives reading more
and writing themselves,

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:45.363
which we think is really important.

00:04:47.030 --> 00:04:51.363
So it's our deepest hope today
that this presentation inspires all

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:53.303
of you -- kids, moms,
dads and teachers --

00:04:55.930 --> 00:04:56.526
to read the Exquisite Corpse if you
haven't read it on Read.gov yet,

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:02.733
and play the progressive
story game yourself.

00:05:03.580 --> 00:05:05.163
You know, at home when you're
all wrapped up in the blankets

00:05:05.930 --> 00:05:06.346
in winter, you can
share stories together

00:05:08.180 --> 00:05:08.450
on those really long car trips when
you're about to kill each other

00:05:12.310 --> 00:05:12.930
in the car -- that's when you want
to share those stories together.

00:05:16.090 --> 00:05:16.536
And it's important to
write your own stories

00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:18.830
and share them with people you love.

00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:23.256
And I am really pleased
to announce today

00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:28.080
that the Exquisite Corps Adventure
is going to be made into a book.

00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:31.693
And it will be published
next fall by Candle of Press,

00:05:31.740 --> 00:05:34.606
right in time for next
year's book festival.

00:05:35.850 --> 00:05:36.850


00:05:37.490 --> 00:05:40.623
And all of our authors
on stage, coincidentally,

00:05:40.850 --> 00:05:40.896
are also contributors to
this incredible anthology

00:05:44.070 --> 00:05:45.870
that the NCBLA put together

00:05:46.070 --> 00:05:46.386
about our White House connecting
literacy to historical literacy.

00:05:50.020 --> 00:05:53.220
It's won every award
imaginable in the last year,

00:05:53.300 --> 00:05:53.496
and it has a brand new piece
at the end of it written

00:05:56.570 --> 00:05:59.703
by poet Nikki Grimes about
her experience coming

00:05:59.910 --> 00:06:00.093
to the historic inauguration
of President Obama,

00:06:02.860 --> 00:06:03.896
which is the new edition
that updates the book,

00:06:04.890 --> 00:06:07.290
the new piece that updates the book.

00:06:07.420 --> 00:06:07.553
So make sure that you find this.

00:06:09.420 --> 00:06:10.306
And when our authors are
illustrating between noon

00:06:11.800 --> 00:06:15.066
and 1 o'clock, they have
also very graciously said

00:06:15.410 --> 00:06:16.703
that they will sign copies of
our White House, if you want them

00:06:18.250 --> 00:06:21.250
to sign that besides
their own terrific books.

00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:25.956
Now, those programs that you all
have, open them up to the inside

00:06:27.770 --> 00:06:30.836
and if you have a red
star inside your program,

00:06:31.940 --> 00:06:35.273
you have just won your own
copy of our White House,

00:06:35.560 --> 00:06:38.826
Looking in Looking out,
and where are the books --

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.133
are over there in the corner.

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:44.390
If you will take your program.

00:06:44.390 --> 00:06:47.923
At the end of the presentation,
you take your program,

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:53.120
and you will get a free book with --

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:56.546
thank you Candle of Press

00:06:58.390 --> 00:07:01.390
for providing free books
for our guests today.

00:07:04.280 --> 00:07:06.013
&gt;&gt; John Cole: Mary Brigid?

00:07:06.280 --> 00:07:07.613
&gt;&gt; Mary Brigid: Yes?

